## {{npmName}}@{{npmVersion}}

This generator creates TypeScript/JavaScript client that utillzes [axios](http://github.com/axios/axios). The generated Node module can be used in the following environments:

Environments
* Node.js
* Webpack
* Browserify

Language level
* ESS - you must have a Promise/A+ library installed
* ES6

Module system
* CommonJS
* ES6 module system

It can be used in both TypeScript and JavaScript. In TypeScript, the definition will be automatically resolved via `package.json`. ([Reference](http://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/declaration-files/consumption.html))

### Building

To build and compile the typescript sources to javascript use:
```
npm install
npm run build
```

### Publishing

First build the package then run `npm publish`

### Consuming

navigate to the folder of your consuming project and run one of the following commands.

_published:_

```
npm install {{npmName}}@{{npmVersion}} --save
```

_unPublished (not recommended):_

```
npm install PATH_TO_GENERATED_PACKAGE --save
```
